feat: track Felo binding attempts, limit user retries and timeout
- Reorganize imports in `discord.rs` to group `chrono` related imports together - Add `felo_binding_history` field to `Data` struct in `discord.rs` to track user binding attempts - Initialize `felo_binding_history` in `init` function in `discord.rs` - Add tracking of user binding attempts and limiting attempts to 3 within 24 hours in `felosearchpro` function in `felo.rs` - Add timeout functionality for users who exceed 3 binding attempts within 24 hours in `felosearchpro` function in `felo.rs` - Add `count` parameter to `validate_user` function in `felo.rs` to handle binding attempt limits - Add simple email format check in `validate_user` function in `felo.rs` - Handle too many binding attempts and email already bound errors in `validate_user` function in `felo.rs`
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 Jim <jim@miniasp.com>

refactor: refactor FeloHandler to optimize role adjustment logic
- Remove unused `HashSet` import - Refactor `review_discord_users` to use new return values from `prepare_data_for_review_discord_users` - Change sleep duration in `review_discord_users` from 1 hour to 1 day - Refactor `prepare_data_for_review_discord_users` to return `Result` and new data structures - Refactor `review` function to use new data structures `Vec<(Member, Email)>` and `Vec<Email>` - Update `adjust_discord_role` to accept new data structures `Vec<Member>` - Update test `review_identifies_users_to_add_and_remove` to `review_correctly_identifies_members` - Update test `review_handles_empty_bindings_and_pro_list` to reflect new data structures - Remove redundant test `review_handles_no_users_to_add_or_remove`
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 Jim <jim@miniasp.com>
